<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Windows 8, Temp Profiles and Other Oddities.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=123&amp;p=460#p460"><![CDATA[
I think Windows will try to create a temp profile if the current profile is corrupted or inaccessible. Maybe your network connection is spotty and it fails to download your remote settings. Are you using a local or Microsoft account?<br /><br />Doesn't seem related to Classic Shell though. To be sure, switch the ClassicShellService to manual and that will disable everything that runs on startup.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2">Ivo</a> — Mon Jan 21, 2013 8:19 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
